Title: Cloudflare API Token Policy (Module-Scoped Only)

Rule:
- Do not use `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN` (generic). Ever.
- Use module-scoped tokens only:
  - APP → `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN_APP`
  - ADMIN → `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN_ADMIN`
  - APEX → `CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN_APEX`
- Scripts must resolve the module by `CF_MODULE` (app|admin|apex) or by `CF_DOMAIN` mapping:
  - app.cloudcache.ai, staging-app.cloudcache.ai → app
  - admin.cloudcache.ai, staging-admin.cloudcache.ai → admin
  - cloudcache.ai, staging-apex.cloudcache.ai, www.cloudcache.ai → apex
- If the module token is missing, fail fast.

Examples:
- `CF_MODULE=app bash scripts/access-verify.sh app.cloudcache.ai /tmp/svc-app.json`
- `CF_DOMAIN=admin.cloudcache.ai bash scripts/access-app-policies.sh admin.cloudcache.ai`

